OL,3,CStarmer says Gorton and Denton by-
OL,4,Celection result is 'very disappointing'
OL,6,FLabour MPs, unions and campaign groups
OL,7,Fhave demanded a change of course from
OL,8,Fthe PM ahead of crucial elections in
OL,9,FMay, with warnings his days in No 10
OL,10,Fcould be numbered unless the party's
OL,11,Ffortunes improve.
OL,13,FFormer Labour deputy leader Angela
OL,14,FRayner said the result should be a
OL,15,F"wake-up call" for the party, calling
OL,16,Ffor her colleagues to "be braver" and
OL,17,F"rededicate" themselves to "a Labour
OL,18,Fagenda that puts people first".
